title: I-CARE Archives
cleaned_text: RSV is a very contagious RNA virus that is usually mild but can also lung inflammation. RSV is also called croup or bronciolitis in children. RSV is spread by droplets from coughing and sneezing and people are usually contagious for 3-8 days. The FLCCC has treatment protocols for both prevention and treatment of RSV.
